<sec id="id-1f923969-0cd6-40c2-e1fb-ff0d0cbce833"><title><bold><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="cf794728-41ee-40f3-ea0d-11340bd896c9" timestamp="1670319527928"?>Gender <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="cf794728-41ee-40f3-ea0d-11340bd896c9"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="89182548-3134-4333-99e3-43b638c12117" text="P" timestamp="1670319528044"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="67492317-c7db-4892-e304-1706f4b4e0bd" timestamp="1670319528477"?>p<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="67492317-c7db-4892-e304-1706f4b4e0bd"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="942ebdcd-1e26-4841-868f-38896178b3e0" timestamp="1667318396588"?>arity of persons taking part in round tables, meetings, conferences and debates<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="942ebdcd-1e26-4841-868f-38896178b3e0"?></bold></title><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="8721099e-f68f-411d-f7e6-f6d982f0b5aa" text="[Former Box 26]" timestamp="1675427000233"?><p><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="a22d609a-9827-413e-a551-e8388427784d" timestamp="1667318500868"?>Following a call by public figures who refused to take part in public events or debates that did not include both <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="a22d609a-9827-413e-a551-e8388427784d"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="9276395" change-id="698399c1-80bb-4ace-d350-929206ecb109" timestamp="1669040440240"?>wo<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="698399c1-80bb-4ace-d350-929206ecb109"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="4146484f-8b10-4edf-ef72-c3a449f0bae5" timestamp="1667318500868"?>men and <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="4146484f-8b10-4edf-ef72-c3a449f0bae5"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="9276395" change-id="2611c480-fd12-4a27-b896-13bdb7be73ee" text="wo" timestamp="1669040442271"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="b8cfce0c-fbcf-4eed-a43a-af542feab8f0" timestamp="1667318500868"?>men, an association was created to guarantee gender equality and the representiveness of women in public speaking.</p><p>The association is co-chaired by a <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="b8cfce0c-fbcf-4eed-a43a-af542feab8f0"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="8848353" change-id="810a9205-c6a2-4f39-88dd-041ebc39d297" timestamp="1670319551599"?>womand and a <?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="810a9205-c6a2-4f39-88dd-041ebc39d297"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="251e6a0e-8c2f-4ddf-9a4e-2bee697983bf" timestamp="1667318500868"?>man<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="251e6a0e-8c2f-4ddf-9a4e-2bee697983bf"?><?fontoxml-change-deletion author-id="8848353" change-id="c9384465-d459-441e-ef55-930fbbbd3071" text=" and a woman" timestamp="1670319553374"?><?fontoxml-change-addition-start author-id="5191008" change-id="573358e7-dd2e-492d-c8e5-ee5f5a4058ed" timestamp="1667318500868"?> and includes leading figures from all areas of life. These public figures agree to not take part in round tables, conferences and debates unless the parity of the participants can be guaranteed. The goal is to prevent and avoid the absence of female speakers.</p><p>The association also labels events that guarantee the active presence of women on all their panels and in all their events, and that promote their competence, irrespective of the subject. Organizing bodies sign a commitment charter in order to receive this label. The organization should guarantee equal representation, or, when this is not possible, gender-based participation that is representative of the personnel based on gender ratios<?fontoxml-change-addition-end change-id="573358e7-dd2e-492d-c8e5-ee5f5a4058ed"?></p><p/></sec>